main event: A civilian reported observing a bright light in the sky over Wayne, Pennsylvania, on September 25, 1965.
interesting points: The observer considered the light to be an extremely bright star that appeared to move constantly about the horizon., The observer believed the object moved back and forth and increased in altitude., A report from October 8, 1965, mentioned a round object resembling a bright meteor with a tail seen by Mrs. Kathryn B. Haaagap., There were several lights that seemed to separate and then come back together in the sighting by Haaagap., The Navy had no records of unusual activity in the area during the sighting timeframe.
sighted object: extremely bright light in the sky
